    "content_hash": "5a09afc734e0bf0e",
    "department": "Design",
    "description": "Tempo is a layer-1 blockchain purpose-built for stablecoins and real-world payments, born from Stripe’s experience in global payments and Paradigm’s expertise in crypto tech.\n\nTempo’s payment-first design provides a scalable, low-cost predictable backbone that meets the needs of high-volume payment use cases. Our goal is to move money reliably, cheaply, and at scale. Our north star is simplicity for users: fintechs, traditional banks, merchants, platforms, and anyone else looking to move their payments into the 21st century.\n\nWe're building Tempo with design partners who are global leaders in AI, e-commerce, and financial services: Anthropic, Coupang, Deutsche Bank, DoorDash, Mercury, Nubank, OpenAI, Revolut, Shopify, Standard Chartered, Visa, and more.\n\nWe’re a team of crypto-optimists, building the infrastructure needed to bring real, substantial economic flows onchain. We like to move fast and swing for the fences — join us!\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nTempo is looking for a Senior Brand Designer to join our creative team and help shape our visual brand world. This is a rare opportunity to do high impact work, bringing a new brand to life and seeing your creative fingerprints across every touchpoint.\n\nYou'll report directly to the Creative Director and work across a wide range of projects, from brand campaigns to everyday go-to-market assets. You're someone who thrives with ownership, moves with intention, and knows how to bring a brand idea all the way through to execution.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL WORK ON\n\n - Brand identity and campaign development\n\n - Merchandise and packaging\n\n - Event design and experiential\n\n - Social content and digital assets\n\n - Go-to-market and marketing collateral\n\n\nWHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR\n\nExperience \u0026 Skills\n\n - 5–8+ years of experience in brand design, with a strong portfolio that reflects it\n\n - Deep expertise in Figma and the Adobe Creative Suite\n\n - Experience working cross-functionally with product and engineering teams\n\n - Comfortable operating independently. You don't need a lot of hand-holding to deliver great work\n\n - Working knowledge of AI-powered creative tools\n\n - Bonus: web development skills\n\nMindset\n\n - A self-starter who takes initiative and owns their work end to end\n\n - Equally comfortable going wide (concept and strategy) and going deep (craft and execution)\n\n - Calm under ambiguity. You can prioritize, adapt, and deliver in a fast-moving environment\n\n - A collaborator at heart, even when working independently\n\n\nWHY TEMPO\n\n - Direct impact on an early-stage brand at a pivotal moment\n\n - Report directly to the Creative Director, your voice carries weight\n\n - Diverse, high-visibility work across brand, product, events, and more\n\n - A creative team that takes the work seriously and has fun doing it",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
